name: Hamilton County Public Health
tweet: Children 5-11 who were vaccinated in early November are due (or coming due) for their 2nd dose (21 days after 1st dose).  Both doses are needed to achieve full effectiveness of the COVID-19 vaccine. Visit  https://t.co/TMglpkNCym to find a location near you.  https://t.co/0iPegcfopp

name: Hamilton County Public Health
tweet: We are monitoring emerging information on the Omicron variant. While it has not been identified in Hamilton County, our message remains to take preventative measures: get vaccinated, get boosted, wear a mask, distance when possible, and wash your hands.   https://t.co/TMglpkNCym  https://t.co/3f9OHUyZDP

name: Hamilton County Public Health
tweet: World AIDS Day (12/1) is dedicated to raising awareness of the AIDS pandemic caused by the spread of HIV infection and mourning those who have died of the disease. We are accepting donations for the Community Engagement Event. Help us give back to the community this #WorldAIDSDay  https://t.co/ppcZvFpC9I

name: Hamilton County Public Health
tweet: Anyone 18 or older can now get a booster dose of the COVID-19 vaccine. We welcome anyone needing a booster dose at any of our clinics ( https://t.co/TMglpkNCym).   When can you get a booster? 2 months after single dose of J&J or 6 months after 2nd dose of Pfizer or Moderna.  https://t.co/hV8a67zRSk
